axsmap.components.Donate.mainTitle: Open more doors for more people.
axsmap.components.Donate.mainMessage: By donating, youre enabling AXS Lab to do the work we do best - bringing people together and creating a world for everyone. Donations mean growing accessibility freedom for all, and helping real people - millions of them - in very real ways.
axsmap.components.Donate.giveCta2Descrip: Choose an amount to give monthly
axsmap.components.Donate.jasonMessage: When diagnosed with primary progressive multiple sclerosis at 25, filmmaker Jason DaSilva turned to art and storytelling, winning an Emmy for the film that told of his journey from cane, to walker, to wheelchair, When I Walk. Today, Jason is an acclaimed director, producer, writer, disability rights activist, and founder of AXS Lab. His goal? To spread awareness through stories, tools, and art, ultimately growing the world to include more experiences and more freedom for everyone.
axsmap.components.ThankYouReview.details: Thank you for contributing to the AXS Map community. With your help and knowledge, were one rating closer to a world with more of the experiences we love - experiences for everyone.
axsmap.components.ThankYouReview.textPla: Review this venue to add photos
axsmap.components.CreateReview.permanent: A ramp is an inclined plane installed in addition to or instead of stairs.
axsmap.components.CreateReview.portableR: A ramp is an inclined plane installed in addition to or instead of stairs.
axsmap.components.CreateReview.noStepsDe: The entrance to the venue has no steps.
axsmap.components.CreateReview.oneStepDe: Any number of steps can seriously limit the possibility of easy navigation for wheelchairs, walkers, and other modes of mobility.
axsmap.components.CreateReview.twoStepsD: Any number of steps can seriously limit the possibility of easy navigation for wheelchairs, walkers, and other modes of mobility.
axsmap.components.CreateReview.threeStep: Any number of steps can seriously limit the possibility of easy navigation for wheelchairs, walkers, and other modes of mobility.
axsmap.components.CreateReview.reservedP: Reserved parking spots at least 96 in. wide with adjacent access aisles, and built on the shortest accessible route of travel from the point of parking to the venue entrance. Marked with the standard blue accessibility logo.
axsmap.components.CreateReview.wideEntra: For a wheelchair to comfortably fit through a doorway,  the doorway should be 32 inches wide. Commonly, doorways measure about 23 to 27 inches wide; this would not be wide enough for a wheelchair to fit through.
axsmap.components.CreateReview.roomToMov: The aisles between fixed seats must be at least 36 inches wide, and restaurants should provide wheelchair accessible seats throughout the dining room.
axsmap.components.CreateReview.accessibl: The surface height should be no more than 34 inches and no less than 28 inches above the floor.
axsmap.components.CreateReview.brightLig: The venue is well-lit, and bright enough to easily navigate.
axsmap.components.CreateReview.highNoise: The venue is at times slightly noisy, or louder than average.
axsmap.components.CreateReview.interiorR: A route inside of a building which slopes measurably from one flat surface to another. The ramp must be at least 36 in. wide.
axsmap.components.CreateReview.accessibl: Elevator doors should measure at least 36 inches, the depth of the elevator 51, and the width at least 68. The entrance and exit to and from the elevator must be readily accessible.
axsmap.components.CreateReview.interiorS: The venue has at least one set of stairs inside the venue.
axsmap.components.CreateReview.walkUpDes: A building or venue which allows access to the upper floors only by stairs, with no elevator available.
axsmap.components.CreateReview.doorSwing: Current guidelines for bathrooms allow the bathroom door to swing inward as long as there is a clear floor space beyond the door swing, when open.
Current guidelines for bathrooms allow the bathroom door to swing inward as long as there is a clear floor space beyond the door swing, when open.
axsmap.components.CreateReview.averageSt: Any floorspace under 30 x 48 inches, or without sufficient room for a wheelchair next to the toilet.
axsmap.components.CreateReview.largeStal: The minimum floorspace should be 30 inches by 48 inches, with plenty of room for a wheelchair next to the toilet.
axsmap.components.CreateReview.loweredSi: Sinks mounted no more than 34 inches from the floor.
axsmap.components.CreateReview.oneBarAro: Metal handrail mounted on the wall beside the toilet.
axsmap.components.CreateReview.twoBarAro: Metal handrail mounted on the wall behind the toilet.
axsmap.components.CreateReview.roomForSe: For bathrooms with large stalls and outward-swinging doors, or extremely large stalls regardless of the door.
axsmap.components.CreateReview.secondEnt: An establishment with more than one entry point to the interior.
axsmap.components.CreateReview.ratingsDe: Each screen will provide you with the opportunity to rate a venue based on a single factor. Take a look at your venue and assess according to the guidelines provided. You may rate all of the factors, or skip as needed. A full rating is not required.
After assessing your venue, simply tap YES or NO.
If you are unsure about a factor, you may skip that entry by using the navigational arrows. When you are finished, tap EXIT REVIEW or the X at the top of your screen to submit your review.
axsmap.components.CreateReview.endReview: Click on the Exit Review button below to submit your review
axsmap.components.Venues.usesMessage1: Our icon system lets you determine at a glance how users have rated a venue for accessibility, across three different phases.
axsmap.components.Venues.whyDescription: To review a place, either search for the venue in the search bar and map or find it on the menu list view, then click Add Review.
axsmap.components.Venues.whyDescription1: With your stories & knowledge, we can grow  this world to create more of the experiences we love - experiences for everyone.
